content:
When setting up an SMS channel, you can now register 10-digit long code numbers and toll-free long code numbers on the new Regulatory Compliance page in Setup. Previously, a web form was used to register numbers, and you couldn’t see your registration status.

Where: This change applies to standard and enhanced SMS channels. View required editions.

How: Follow the instructions to open a case requesting your new SMS channel. When your case is closed, it’s time to register your number or numbers. In Setup, go to the Regulatory Compliance page under Messaging. Click Register Long Code to register a US or Canadian 10-digit long code number, or click Register Toll-Free to register a toll-free long code number.

The registration timeline isn’t affected by this change. Registering a new phone number in the US and Canada can take 1 to 2 weeks for toll-free numbers and 1 to 4 weeks for 10-digit long codes.
title: Registering Long Codes for SMS Channels
